https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZknwxYH8g2A

Ingredients:
200g Paneer
1.5 cup peas (can increase)
2-4 potatoes
2 red onions, diced
2-3 large tomatoes, diced
4 cloves garlic (eyeball)
2 inches of ginger, peeled 
10 cashews
1tsp cumin
1/2 inch cinnamon
3 pods green cardamom
serrano peppers 2-3
thai chilli peppers 4-10 (to taste)
1/2 tsp turmeric
1 tsp chili powder
1/2 tsp coriander powder
1/2 tsp cumin powder
1/2 tsp garam masala
1 tsp salt 
2tbsp cream (can maybe use yogurt, havent tried)
1 tsp kasuri methi (havent used yet)
2 tbsp cilantro

heat oil in pot 
cook onions, ginger, and garlic until close to caramelized/caramelized
add diced tomatoes and cashews
saute until mush

remove from heat, cool, blitz in food processor until a paste

rinse out pot

add oil + ghee to pot
add cumin, cinnamon, cardamom, and chili peppers to pot
saute until aromatic
add turmeric powder, chili powder, coriander powder, cumin powder, garam masala, 
saute until aromatic

add onion tomato mixture, fry and stir until color change (should turn a deeper color, mixture should be bubbling and thicken and become almost reddish with oil separating)

add 3 cups of water and salt
mix
bring to boil, can thicken a little bit here too (thickense overnight in fridge)

add 1.5 cups of peas, add cubed paneer (optionally: lightly fry paneer in separate pan with julienned ginger before adding)
mix

simmer for 5 minutes with lid on

add cream, kasuri methi, and cilantro

mix, youre done :)

